        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 4:17PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 7 miles southeast of Edna to 2 miles southeast of
Watova. Movement was northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
New Alluwe...                     Watova...
Centralia...                      Nowata...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
